Step 1: Calculate Debt to Equity Ratio  
• Total Liabilities are given as the sum of Accounts Payable and Taxes Payable (“Total Current Liabilities”): 624988.48.  
• Total Owner's Equity is provided as: 14903401.82.  
• Debt to Equity Ratio = 624988.48 / 14903401.82 ≈ 0.04193, which rounds to 0.04.

Step 2: Calculate Net Profit Margin  
• Net Profit (from the income statement) = 1903401.82.  
• Total Revenue (from the income statement) = 4879769.51.  
• Net Profit Margin = (1903401.82 / 4879769.51) × 100 ≈ 39.00%.

Step 3: Calculate Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio  
• Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities (from the cash flow statement) = -862455.97.  
• Total Current Liabilities = 624988.48.  
• Ratio = -862455.97 / 624988.48 ≈ -1.38.

Thus, the answer in JSON format is:
{"solution": {"Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.04", "Net Profit Margin": "39.00%", "operating cash flow to current liabilities ratio": "-1.38"}}
